<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>The <a href="https://jcp.org/en/jsr/detail?id=316">Java EE 6 proposal</a> (JSR 316) was published today. I believe that this will be the most important revision of the platform since it was released nearly 10 years ago, and that it should be welcomed by users of the technology. Interface21 is happy to be a supporter of this JSR, and I am looking forward to contributing to it.</p>
<p>Java EE (known as J2EE for most of its history) has played a valuable role in creating a market for Java middleware. However, over those 10 years, important issues have emerged with the platform, such as:<br> </p>
</div>
</section>
